{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b45093b-059d-4deb-8924-92e6445b5084","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3's MTP runner) — **or** if you want to stay on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead (available from xunit 2.9.3+).\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes your test project a standalone app).\n\n**Summary of package changes:**\n\n| Remove | Add |\n|---|---|\n| `xunit.runner.visualstudio` | `xunit.runner.mtp` (for xUnit v2) |\n\n> **Tip:** If you're open to upgrading to xUnit v3, replace `xunit` with `xunit.v3` and use `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` instead — v3 has native MTP support and is the recommended path forward.\n\nWould you like help applying these changes to a specific `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"07113f01-3735-4312-9abe-99f2d0be655d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":386,"requestId":"042C:D1352:1DAEEE2:2177D57:69E8194F"},"id":"ea279c04-df1a-420c-a356-ae26544d1e8f","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:03.971Z","parentId":"2183d63a-85af-42d6-b78f-7d99cf5011bf"}
